{"content": "<h2>The Artist: David Loh</h2>\t\t\n\t\t<p>David joined the cryptoart revolution in March 2022, bringing his sharp perspective for areas the rest of us merely traverse when getting from a to b. Those middle spaces are where David's art practice thrives. </p>\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<figure>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<img width=\"749\" height=\"562\" src=\"https://digital-artist-economy.ghost.io/content/images/2024/11/aesrial-10-David-Loh-1024x768.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://digital-artist-economy.ghost.io/content/images/2024/11/aesrial-10-David-Loh-1024x768.jpg 1024w, https://digital-artist-economy.ghost.io/content/images/2024/11/aesrial-10-David-Loh-300x225.jpg 300w, https://digital-artist-economy.ghost.io/content/images/2024/11/aesrial-10-David-Loh-768x576.jpg 768w, https://digital-artist-economy.ghost.io/content/images/2024/11/aesrial-10-David-Loh-1536x1152.jpg 1536w, https://digital-artist-economy.ghost.io/content/images/2024/11/aesrial-10-David-Loh-2048x1536.jpg 2048w, https://digital-artist-economy.ghost.io/content/images/2024/11/aesrial-10-David-Loh-400x300.jpg 400w, https://digital-artist-economy.ghost.io/content/images/2024/11/aesrial-10-David-Loh-1320x990.jpg 1320w, https://digital-artist-economy.ghost.io/content/images/2024/11/aesrial-10-David-Loh-600x450.jpg 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 749px) 100vw, 749px\" />\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<figcaption>aesrial #10 by David Loh</figcaption>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</figure>\n\t\t\t\t\t<blockquote>\n\t\t\t<p>\n\t\t\t\t\"Seeking meaning in vague scenes and immaterial spaces.\"\t\t\t</p>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<cite>David Loh</cite>\n\t\t\t\t\t</blockquote>\n\t\t\t<h2>The Collection: Aesthetics of the Immaterial</h2>\t\t\n\t\t<p>Aesthetics of the Immaterial frames the forgotten in provocative ways to recalibrate what we had missed on our travels to date. The angular steps, the yellow laddered caution and the sliver of sky all feel like a form of trap in Loh's work. As if the lens is both inviting us there with perspective, yet with alarm bells sounding. Loh's work is unafraid of simplicity, instead seeking out the spaces where the architects had decided no pomp or frill necessary.</p>\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<img width=\"749\" height=\"686\" src=\"https://digital-artist-economy.ghost.io/content/images/2024/11/Aesthetics-of-the-Immaterial-collection-David-Loh-1024x938.png\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://digital-artist-economy.ghost.io/content/images/2024/11/Aesthetics-of-the-Immaterial-collection-David-Loh-1024x938.png 1024w, https://digital-artist-economy.ghost.io/content/images/2024/11/Aesthetics-of-the-Immaterial-collection-David-Loh-300x275.png 300w, https://digital-artist-economy.ghost.io/content/images/2024/11/Aesthetics-of-the-Immaterial-collection-David-Loh-768x703.png 768w, https://digital-artist-economy.ghost.io/content/images/2024/11/Aesthetics-of-the-Immaterial-collection-David-Loh-600x549.png 600w, https://digital-artist-economy.ghost.io/content/images/2024/11/Aesthetics-of-the-Immaterial-collection-David-Loh.png 1210w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 749px) 100vw, 749px\" />\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t<h2>A Specific Artwork: aesrial #15 'high life'</h2>\t\t\n\t\t<p>The persistence of balance continues in 'aesrial #15' where every component feels manufactured for theatrics. Even the pleasantries of entertainment here could not seem more perfunctory. It is in this absurdity, that Loh is saying something about those who inhabit these spaces that is non-obvious to them.</p>\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<figure>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<img width=\"749\" height=\"500\" src=\"https://digital-artist-economy.ghost.io/content/images/2024/11/aesrial-15-david-loh-1024x683.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://digital-artist-economy.ghost.io/content/images/2024/11/aesrial-15-david-loh-1024x683.jpg 1024w, https://digital-artist-economy.ghost.io/content/images/2024/11/aesrial-15-david-loh-300x200.jpg 300w, https://digital-artist-economy.ghost.io/content/images/2024/11/aesrial-15-david-loh-768x512.jpg 768w, https://digital-artist-economy.ghost.io/content/images/2024/11/aesrial-15-david-loh-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://digital-artist-economy.ghost.io/content/images/2024/11/aesrial-15-david-loh-2048x1365.jpg 2048w, https://digital-artist-economy.ghost.io/content/images/2024/11/aesrial-15-david-loh-1320x880.jpg 1320w, https://digital-artist-economy.ghost.io/content/images/2024/11/aesrial-15-david-loh-600x400.jpg 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 749px) 100vw, 749px\" />\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<figcaption>aesrial #15 by David Loh collected by MintFace</figcaption>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</figure>\n\t\t\t\t\t<a href=\"https://theline.wtf/listing/david-lacy/\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tDavid Loh | Line 328\n\t\t\t\t\t</a>"}